                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Foliot</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_109459">Rolesham</placeName>
                        </persName>
               and <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Foliot</surname>
                        </persName> his heir, grant to
               <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Bervelie</surname>
                        </persName> for
               his homage and service, one messuage in the village of <placeName key="place_109459">Rolesham</placeName>, viz. that which
               <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Grent</surname>
                        </persName> held, and 9 acres of their 
               demesne in one field, and 9 acres in another, to hold to the said Walter and 
               <persName nymRef="Bervelie">
                           <forename>Alice</forename> his wife</persName> and their heirs.
               And after the decease of the said Walter, they grant to his wife Alice another 9 acres in one
               field, and 9 acres in another, so that she has 18 acres in each, paying annually one
               pound of cummin. Also they grant common of pasture for cattle that feed within their lordship. 
               (<origDate notBefore="1190" notAfter="1200" precision="low">c. 1190-1200</origDate>.) 
               . </p>
